<section id="oss" class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Open Source</h2>
    <p class="section-note">Open-source projects I contribute to.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card feature-card">
    <h3>OpenClaw</h3>
    <p>
      Open-source AI assistant project I contribute to.
    </p>
    <p class="links-row">
      <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Project →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="nested-section">
      <p class="card-label">Selected Contributions</p>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>Telegram non-streaming media deduplication</h4>
        <p>
          Fixed duplicate <code>MEDIA:</code> attachment delivery in Telegram non-streaming mode by
          tracking block-sent media URLs, filtering final reply payloads, and covering the pure
          deduplication path with regression tests.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/78420" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>TUI streaming watchdog reconnect recovery</h4>
        <p>
          Resynced the TUI streaming watchdog after reconnects, kept active tool and
          lifecycle events as proof-of-life, and added regression coverage for stale
          reconnect runs.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/74224" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>WhatsApp DM voice-note transcription</h4>
        <p>
          Restored preflight speech-to-text for WhatsApp DM voice notes so agents receive
          spoken text instead of raw <code>&lt;media:audio&gt;</code> placeholders when transcription succeeds.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/64120" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>Heartbeat session key canonicalization</h4>
        <p>
          Prevented runaway <code>:heartbeat</code> suffix accumulation in isolated sessions,
          added stale-key cleanup, and covered the behavior with regression tests.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/59606" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>Browser launch blank-tab fix</h4>
        <p>
          Removed an unintended extra blank tab on browser launch by fixing launch arguments and
          locking the behavior with a regression test.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/52451" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card feature-card">
    <h3>OpenChronicle</h3>
    <p>
      Open-source personal knowledge management with LLM-powered memory compaction.
    </p>
    <p class="links-row">
      <a href="https://github.com/Einsia/OpenChronicle" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Project →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="nested-section">
      <p class="card-label">Selected Contributions</p>

      <div class="nested-card">
        <h4>Compact overwriting concurrent writes fix</h4>
        <p>
          <code>compact_file</code> LLM rewrite could overwrite entries appended by concurrent
          reducers. Added compare-and-swap writeback: re-read the file under per-file lock before
          writing, skip compaction if changed, and refresh FTS rows atomically inside a SQLite
          savepoint.
        </p>
        <p class="links-row">
          <a href="https://github.com/Einsia/OpenChronicle/pull/25" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View PR →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
